Kris:

PrivilegedAccessor.invokeMethod() derives the method parameter types
from the values - there&#39;s simply no way to do this if a value is null. 
However you should be able to do something like this:

Method m = PrivilegedAccessor.getMethod(child, &quot;myMethod&quot;, 
        new Class[] {Integer.class, String.class});
m.invoke(someInstance, new Object[] {null, &quot;hello&quot;});

- Jim Yingst

